options.caption: This is a human nerve cell
options.imageAlt: This colorful, magnified image of a human nerve cell shows the cell's distinctive structure. It has a rounded central cell body with slender extensions spreading outward in many directions.

options.caption: This photo shows a tissue of the fungus Histoplasma
options.imageAlt: In this magnified image, lung tissue appears as pink spherical shapes mixed into a white surface. Some of the pink shapes are enlarged and almost black in color.

options.caption: Chickens and other birds have an organ called a gizzard, which helps them digest food.
Parts of the root systems of the many species of mangrove trees are above ground. The aboveground roots serve different purposes, including intake of oxygen.
options.imageAlt: This photograph shows the distinctive root systems of mangrove trees. The roots arch outward from the tree above the water's surface, and extend downward into the water.
